com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.process

Class ProcessOutputStreamSettingsAfterStart

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.process.ProcessOutputStreamSettings
      • com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.process.ProcessOutputStreamSettingsAfterStart

  • @FullyTested
public class ProcessOutputStreamSettingsAfterStart
extends ProcessOutputStreamSettings
    This simple class holds the settings for child process output streams (either STDOUT or STDERR) after the child process starts. After the child process has started, certain output stream settings (for STDOUT or STDERR) cannot be reasonably changed, e.g., charCallbackFactory(FuncUtils.Func0). This subclass implements no new behavior except to throw UnsupportedOperationException for certain restricted setter methods.

    This class may not be instantiated directly. Normally, only class AbstractProcessSettings creates instances.

    The following methods throw UnsupportedOperationException:

    • charCallbackFactory(FuncUtils.Func0)
    • byteCallbackFactory(FuncUtils.Func0)
    Author:
    Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)

    • Method Detail

      • charCallbackFactory

        public ProcessOutputStreamSettings charCallbackFactory(FuncUtils.Func0<Appendable> optCallbackFactory)
        Always throws UnsupportedOperationException. As the child process starts, the character-based callback factory is used to create a new callback.

        Sets the factory to create a new character-based callback. The initial value is null.

        If the character-based callback has state, such as StringBuffer, and multiple child processes are started from a single ProcessBuilder2, a factory should instead be used.

        All calls to this method clear previous settings to ProcessOutputStreamSettings.charCallback(Appendable).
